result.adr_address: 406 - 410, 128 Carpenter Rd, Kowloon City, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 406 - 410, 128 Carpenter Rd, Kowloon City, Hong Kong
result.name: Speedway Diner

reviews.text: Great place for kids. We ordered a bunch of combo meals for a weeknight dinner so the kiddos could have 30ish minutes of track time each. It was not too crowded.  There are also a few basic arcade games to play while waiting / eating.  FYI we saw some cars which can be remote controlled by parents if the kids are too young to know how to "drive".

Wish the operators were better organised and more clear with the offer. It took quite a long time to explain to each customer and only one cashier. In the end we still didn’t get what we ordered ... and not that we wanted less, the order that came out was wrong and we had to order more. Meal was very ordinary quality considering the prices ... for example $86 (with tax) for spaghetti bolognaise, meant to be for adult taste and portion.

Suggest that given the size of the track and range of other games, and meal quality, more suited to younger customers ... under 12, birthday parties and groups.

Also, it seems that even though there are automatic table assignments for walk-in, you can request to change for a better position (to see the track) to the disadvantage of the next customer ... I think that was quite unfair.

Good sized track and the prices are reasonable for a 6 minute ride. Lower cost group and party process available. There is food offered here as well but I can't comment on the food as I haven't tried it.
Excited driving,  but expensive, no speeding here !

It was a birthday party our family attended. The host has arranged matches for the kids, the mums, and the dads. It was so fun. The food was great, too: pizza, pasta, burgers and hotdogs. Everyone enjoyed it very much. It was an amazing night.
